    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>+ In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/126">Cunradus</persName> divina favente clementia Romanorum
                            <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs> secundus. Religiosorum petitionibus
                        aurem pietatis accommodare et, que ad dei cultum pertinent, summo
                        benivolentie studio promovere regie liberalitatis est, cuius honor iudicium
                        diligit, unde in eterna vita condignam bone mercedis retributionem et in
                        temporalis regni administratione gloriam nobis accrescere confidimus.
                        Eapropter omnium tam futurorum quam presentium noverit industria, qualiter
                        quidam <rs key="#Personal_rank">nobilis</rs> homo <persName
                            key="#Personal_rank"><name ref="Ingelscalcus de Sancto Dionisio"
                                >Engelscalcvs videlicet de sancto Dionisio</name></persName>
                        <rs
                            key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            >villam</rs> que dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Villas #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Inflow #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Beneficium"
                            ref="#places/5142"><geogName
                                key="#Rivers #Villas #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Inflow #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Beneficium"
                                ref="#estates/3057">Zvwerendorf</geogName></placeName>, quam a <rs
                            key="#Marquis/duke">marchione</rs>
                        <persName key="#Marquis/duke" ref="#people/5033">Odachario de
                            Stira</persName> in <rs key="#Beneficium">beneficio</rs> tenebat, eidem
                        marchioni resignavit humiliter petens, ut et ipse <rs key="#siblingOf"
                            >fratri</rs> nostro <persName
                            key="#Marquis/duke #Vir_inluster #siblingOf" ref="#people/5034"
                            >Heinrico</persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_inluster">illustri</rs>
                        <rs key="#Bavarian">Bawarorum</rs>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">duci</rs>, a quo ipse eandem villam habebat, pro
                        salute anime sue redderet. Marchio itaque Odacharius iustas predicti nobilis
                        viri preces benigne exaudiens eandem villam fratri nostro Heinrico Bawarorum
                        duci resignavit, sed et frater noster dux, qui eam a nobis et a regno
                        beneficiario iure possidebat, libere et sine omni contradictione sepedictam
                        villam nobis reddidit. Nos ergo ob regni nostri firmam stabilitatem et anime
                        nostre nostrorumque parentum perpetuam salutem prefatam villam cum omnibus
                        suis pertinentiis, id est <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terris cultis et
                            incultis </rs><rs key="#Rivers #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            >aquis aquarumve decursibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">pratis pascuis</rs><rs
                            key="#Forests #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"> silvis</rs> cum
                        omnique utilitate, que inde provenire potest, <rs key="#Churches"
                            >ecclesie</rs> de <orgName key="#Churches #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3805">Runa</orgName> et fratribus ibidem deo et
                        sancte Marie perpetue virgini servientibus in proprietatem absque ullius
                        contradictione donavimus edicto regali precipientes, ne aliqua umquam
                        persona magna seu parva hanc nostram donationem infringat, sed fratres in
                        prefato <rs key="#Monasteries">cenobio</rs> deo famulantes eandem villam
                        proprietario iure omni deinceps tempore libere et pacifice possideant. Si
                        quis vero, quod absit, huius precepti nostri statutum infringere
                        temptaverit, <rs key="#Penalty">centum libras auri puri</rs> componat,
                        quarum partem dimidiam camere nostre, reliquam vero predicte ecclesie
                        persolvat. Ut autem hec rata et inconvulsa permaneant, presentem paginam
                        inde conscriptam sigilli nostri impressione insigniri iussimus manuque
                        propria, ut infra videtur, corroborantes, qui presentes aderant, <rs
                            key="#Witness">testes</rs> subternotari fecimus. Quorum nomina hec sunt:
                            <persName key="#Witness #Bishops" ref="#people/5035">Embricho</persName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/5143">Wirceborgensis</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #Prevosts"><name
                                ref="Otto">Otto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Prevosts">prepositus</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #Prevosts"
                                ><name ref="Gebehardus">Geuehardus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Prevosts">prepositus</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #Prevosts"
                                ><name ref="Sigefridus">Sifridus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Prevosts">prepositus</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #Prevosts"
                                ><name ref="Guntherius">Guntherus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Prevosts">prepositus</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #Princeps"
                            ref="#people/3042">Robertus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Princeps">princeps</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/173">Capuanus</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Count" ref="#people/5036">Rogerius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comes</rs> de <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/4710">Ariana</placeName>, <persName key="#Witness #Count"
                                ><name ref="Richardus">Richardus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comes</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #Count"><name
                                ref="Robertus">Robertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comes</rs>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Walterius von Lobenhausen">Walterus de
                            Louenhuse</name></persName> et <rs key="#siblingOf">frater</rs> eius
                            <persName key="#Witness #siblingOf"><name
                                ref="Ingelhardus von Lobenhausen">Engelhardus</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Wilielmus von Biuerbach">Willehelmus
                                de Biuerbach</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Everardus von Hoenstein">Euerhardus de
                            Hoenstein</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Cuneradus Pris">Cunradus Pris</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Arnaldus von Rotenburg">Arnoldus de
                                Rodenburch</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Rimun von Reinardeshovend">Riwinus de
                            Reinardeshovend</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Robertus de Castella">Robertus de Castella</name></persName>.
                        Signum domini Cunradi Romanorum regis secundi. (M.) (S. sp.) Ego <persName
                            key="#Writer #Chancellor" ref="#people/5037">Arnoldus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> vice <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Archbishops" ref="#people/3728"
                            >Heinrici</persName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/2968">Moguntini</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovi. (SI.) Anno dominice incarnationis
                        MCXLIIII, indictione VII, regnante Cunrado Romanorum rege II, anno vero
                        regni eius VII, data <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/5143"
                            >Wirzeburch</placeName>; in Christo feliciter amen.</ab>
                </div>
